## 🎯 Technical Architecture Deep Dive

### Advanced Storage Architecture (The Crown Jewel)

#### Two-Tier SnapRAID + MergerFS (Current Implementation)
```
Primary Storage Strategy:

NVMe Cache Tier (3TB total):
├── /mnt/cache/appdata/    # Docker databases (PERMANENT - never moved)
├── /mnt/cache/downloads/  # Active downloads (temporary)
├── /mnt/cache/media/      # New media files (24h aging)
└── /mnt/cache/system/     # OS and binaries (PERMANENT)

48TB Array Storage Pool (SnapRAID + MergerFS):
├── 38TB Usable Space (6 data drives: 2TB+4TB+8TB+12TB+6TB+6TB)
├── 10TB Parity Protection (2 drives: 16TB each)
├── 99.99% Data Safety with dual parity
└── Mixed drive optimization maximizes space efficiency
```

#### ZFS Integration & Advanced Storage Tiers

**ZFS vs SnapRAID Positioning**:
```
ZFS Integration (v2.1 Roadmap):
├── Enterprise/Professional Edition Features
├── Advanced Snapshot Management
├── Native Deduplication & Compression
├── Self-Healing with Scrubbing
└── High-Performance Mirror/RAIDZ Pools

ZFS Use Cases:
├── Performance-Critical: Mirror pools for databases
├── Enterprise: RAIDZ2/3 for maximum data integrity  
├── Hybrid: ZFS system pool + SnapRAID for media
└── Advanced: ZFS Send/Receive for replication
```

**Cache Mover Enhancement for ZFS**:
```go
// Multi-tier cache management
type StorageStrategy int
const (
    SnapRAID_MergerFS StorageStrategy = iota
    ZFS_Mixed
    ZFS_Pure
    Hybrid_Advanced
)

// Intelligent storage routing
func (cm *CacheMover) routeToStorage(fileType string, size int64) string {
    switch cm.strategy {
    case ZFS_Mixed:
        if fileType == "database" { return "/zfs/nvme/databases" }
        if size > 50*GB { return "/snapraid/array" }
        return "/zfs/cache"
    case Hybrid_Advanced:
        return cm.aiOptimalPlacement(fileType, size, accessPattern)
    }
}
```

**ZFS Pool Management**:
```bash
# ZFS pool creation with cache tiers
zpool create -o ashift=12 \
  tank mirror nvme0n1 nvme1n1 \
  cache ssd0 ssd1 \
  log nvme2n1p1

# Advanced features
zfs set compression=lz4 tank
zfs set dedup=on tank/databases
zfs create -o recordsize=1M tank/media
```

**Cache Mover Intelligence**:
```go
// Exclusion Rules (Protect Docker databases)
excludePaths := []string{
    "/mnt/cache/appdata/",       // All Docker databases stay on NVMe
    "/mnt/cache/system/",        // System files stay on NVMe
    "/mnt/cache/downloads/*.part", // Incomplete downloads protected
}

// Age-based Movement Rules  
moveRules := map[string]time.Duration{
    "/mnt/cache/media/":    24 * time.Hour,  // Media files
    "/mnt/cache/backup/":   7 * 24 * time.Hour, // Backups
    "/mnt/cache/tmp/":      1 * time.Hour,   // Temp files
}
```

